<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="463" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="6.[1363,2573,277,553]" pageId="6" pageNumber="463">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1366,1712,399,428]" pageId="6" pageNumber="463">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
CITES Appendix II. Classified as Least Concern on The [UCN Red List. Hoffmanns’s Titi is relatively well protected by the isolation of its geographic distribution. It is present in Amazonia National Park and Itaituba National Forest.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
